{
 "fragments": [
  {
   "begin": "0.000",
   "children": [],
   "end": "4.520",
   "id": "f000001",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "They say in the town of Widdershade, people don't cast shadows after sunset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "4.520",
   "children": [],
   "end": "5.600",
   "id": "f000002",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "It's not magic."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "5.600",
   "children": [],
   "end": "6.640",
   "id": "f000003",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "It's Felix."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "6.640",
   "children": [],
   "end": "9.440",
   "id": "f000004",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "Felix Holloway wasn't always a shadow collector."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "9.440",
   "children": [],
   "end": "13.120",
   "id": "f000005",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "He started out as a quiet cobbler with bad eyesight and a worse memory."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "13.120",
   "children": [],
   "end": "20.560",
   "id": "f000006",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "But one cloudy evening, while fixing a boot by candlelight, he noticed something odd - the customer's shadow stepped away from him."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "20.560",
   "children": [],
   "end": "23.800",
   "id": "f000007",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "It yawned, stretched, and disappeared out the window."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "23.800",
   "children": [],
   "end": "24.760",
   "id": "f000008",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "Felix blinked."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "24.760",
   "children": [],
   "end": "25.840",
   "id": "f000009",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "Twice."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "25.840",
   "children": [],
   "end": "28.680",
   "id": "f000010",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "Then did what any sane man would: he followed it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "28.680",
   "children": [],
   "end": "37.960",
   "id": "f000011",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "He chased the shadow through cobbled alleys, up a twisted oak tree, and into a hole behind the apothecary, where - to his absolute confusion - he found a market."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "37.960",
   "children": [],
   "end": "39.040",
   "id": "f000012",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "Not for fruit."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "39.040",
   "children": [],
   "end": "40.200",
   "id": "f000013",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "Not for shoes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "40.200",
   "children": [],
   "end": "41.200",
   "id": "f000014",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "But for shadows."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "41.200",
   "children": [],
   "end": "49.400",
   "id": "f000015",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "Tall ones, crooked ones, shadows that danced when you whistled - all hanging on clotheslines, whispering like curtains in the wind."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "49.400",
   "children": [],
   "end": "53.080",
   "id": "f000016",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "A woman with silver eyes traded hers for twenty extra years of sleep."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "53.080",
   "children": [],
   "end": "55.160",
   "id": "f000017",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "A butcher sold his to forget the war."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "55.160",
   "children": [],
   "end": "57.960",
   "id": "f000018",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "Felix, as it turns out, had a gift."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "57.960",
   "children": [],
   "end": "61.320",
   "id": "f000019",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "He could untie a shadow from your feet like untying a shoelace."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "61.320",
   "children": [],
   "end": "61.880",
   "id": "f000020",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "It made him..."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "61.880",
   "children": [],
   "end": "62.600",
   "id": "f000021",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "popular."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "62.600",
   "children": [],
   "end": "71.000",
   "id": "f000022",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "By the time the moon was high, he'd bought a shadow that told jokes, one that could open locked doors, and another that kept perfect time like a metronome."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "71.000",
   "children": [],
   "end": "72.040",
   "id": "f000023",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "Years passed."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "72.040",
   "children": [],
   "end": "73.720",
   "id": "f000024",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "Felix became a legend."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "73.720",
   "children": [],
   "end": "75.760",
   "id": "f000025",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "People lined up to lighten their burdens."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "75.760",
   "children": [],
   "end": "79.680",
   "id": "f000026",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "To sell the parts of themselves they no longer wanted to carry in the light."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "79.680",
   "children": [],
   "end": "84.000",
   "id": "f000027",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "But one day, a girl came to him and said, \"I want yours.\" He laughed."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "84.000",
   "children": [],
   "end": "84.880",
   "id": "f000028",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "\"Mine?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "84.880",
   "children": [],
   "end": "85.800",
   "id": "f000029",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "It's stubborn."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "85.800",
   "children": [],
   "end": "90.200",
   "id": "f000030",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "Doesn't even follow me properly anymore.\" \"I don't need it to follow,\" she said."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "90.200",
   "children": [],
   "end": "92.840",
   "id": "f000031",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "\"Just to remember.\" Felix was quiet."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "92.840",
   "children": [],
   "end": "96.680",
   "id": "f000032",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "For the first time, he looked behind him - and saw nothing."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "96.680",
   "children": [],
   "end": "98.640",
   "id": "f000033",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "Just a trail of old footsteps."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "98.640",
   "children": [],
   "end": "100.040",
   "id": "f000034",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "And then he realized..."
   ]
  },
  {
   "begin": "100.040",
   "children": [],
   "end": "102.000",
   "id": "f000035",
   "language": "en",
   "lines": [
    "He hadn't seen his shadow in years."
   ]
  }
 ]
}